Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{} for the risotto.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Once hot, add the onion to the pan and stir-fry until caramelised, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim the @courgette{1}, then quarter lengthways. Chop into 2cm chunks. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the onion has caramelised, add the garlic and @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @risotto rice{175%grams} to the onions. Stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}, then stir in the @cider vinegar{15%milliliter} and allow to evaporate, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @boiled water{600%milliliter} for the risotto and @vegetable stock paste{20%grams}. Bring back up to the boil, then pop a lid on the pan (or cover with #foil{}).

Bake the risotto on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{25-30%minutes}.

When the risotto has been in the oven for about ~{10%minutes}, pat the @basa fillets{2} dry with #kitchen paper{} and lay it onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Sprinkle over the @roasted spice and herb blend{1%sachet}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, drizzle over a little @oil{a little}, then rub it into the fish.

Bake the fish on the top shelf of your oven until cooked, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked when opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

When hot, add the courgette and cook until charred, ~{6-8%minutes} total. Turn only every couple of mins.

Once cooked, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then remove from the heat and set aside.

When the risotto is ready, remove it from the oven and stir through the @harissa paste{50%grams}, @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams}, charred courgette and @butter{20%grams}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Share the risotto between your #serving bowls{} and lay the spiced basa on top to finish.

Enjoy!